byline.contributor: Reporting was contributed by Najim Rahim, Fahim Abed, Jawad Sukhanyar and Zahra Nader from Kabul, and Taimoor Shah from Kandahar, Afghanistan.

abstract: Taliban forces infiltrate central neighborhoods in northern city of Kunduz in Afghanistan, in coordinated attack that succeeds despite efforts by struggling Afghan forces and supporting American troops.
lead_paragraph: American officials said resources were being diverted to Kunduz, while the Taliban made gains in a separate assault in Helmand Province in the south.
snippet: American officials said resources were being diverted to Kunduz, while the Taliban made gains in a separate assault in Helmand Province in the south....

headline.main: Emboldened Taliban Overrun Parts of Kunduz and Taunt Afghan Forces
headline.print_headline: Emboldened Taliban Overrun Parts of Key Afghan City and Taunt Government Forces
